## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1c429-147"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> est destinée à être instancié une fois et réutilisées dans l’ensemble de la durée de vie d’une application.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1c429-147"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> is intended to be instantiated once and re-used throughout the life of an application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1c429-148">Le nombre de sockets disponibles en cas de surcharges arriveront à l’instanciation d’une classe de client HTTP pour chaque demande.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1c429-148">Instantiating an HttpClient class for every request will exhaust the number of sockets available under heavy loads.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1c429-149">Cela entraîne des erreurs de SocketException.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1c429-149">This will result in SocketException errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1c429-150">Voici un exemple d’utilisation HttpClient correctement.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1c429-150">Below is an example using HttpClient correctly.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public class GoodController : ApiController  
{  
    // OK  
    private static readonly HttpClient HttpClient;  
  
    static GoodController()  
    {  
        HttpClient = new HttpClient();  
    }  
}  
  
```
